{"lemma":"صِهْرُ","slug":"صِهْرُ","root":"ص.ه.ر","root_slug":"ص-ه-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ه-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"صِهْر","root":"صهر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25066","n25070","n25071"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%90%D9%87%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to smelt"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cook thoroughly, to broil"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of صَهَرَ (ṣahara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"relatedness by marriage, affinity","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a relative through marriage, an in-law","tags":["countable"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25066","headword_ar":"صَهَرَ","root":"Shr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SahorN","text_ar":"صَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He melted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liquefied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing, (S, A, K,) such as fat, (A, TA,) and the like; (TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASThr","text_ar":"اصطهر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) The saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^aSoharan~aka biyamiynK mur~apK","text_ar":"لَاَصْهَرَنَّكَ بِيَمِينٍ مُرَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will assuredly melt thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the fire of Hell"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by"},{"kind":"text","text":"making thee to swear"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bitter oath"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will assuredly make thee to swear a hard oath."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saharotu fulaAnFA biyamiynK kaA*ibapK","text_ar":"صَهَرْتُ فُلَانًا بِيَمِينٍ كَاذِبَةٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuwojibu lahu Aln~aAra","text_ar":"تُوْجِبُ لَهُ النَّارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I caused such a one to melt, by"},{"kind":"text","text":"making him to swear"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a false oath that would procure for him, as a consequence thereof, the fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Hell]. (AO.) ―         -b2-  Also, inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, burned: he thoroughly cooked"},{"kind":"text","text":"with fire. (TA.) ―         -b3-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(heat)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affected him severely."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saharatohu Al$~amosu","text_ar":"صَهَرَتْهُ الشَّمْسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sun affected him severely by its heat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * A, K, * TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that it pained his brain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Ibn-Ahmar says, describing the young one of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaAp","text_ar":"قَطَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) which was bearing water to it, (O,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"tarowiY laqFY A^uloqiYa fiY SafoSafK\n                      \n                     ↓ \n      taSoharuhu Al$~amosu famaA yanoSahiro"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She bearing water to a castaway, cast upon a plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which the sun was melting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"severely affecting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which did not melt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which endured the sun's melting it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * O. [In both of my copies of the S, and in the O and TA, the first word is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarowiY","text_ar":"تَرْوِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", as above; not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turowiY","text_ar":"تُرْوِى"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sahara AlHar~u AlHirobaA='a","text_ar":"صَهَرَ الحَرُّ الحِرْبَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The heat made the chameleon's back to glisten."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sahara xubozahu","text_ar":"صَهَرَ خُبْزَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He seasoned his bread with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuhaArap","text_ar":"صُهَارَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, A, TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"melted fat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sahara raA^osahu","text_ar":"صَهَرَ رَاْسَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He anointed his head with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuhaArap","text_ar":"صُهَارَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sahara badanahu","text_ar":"صَهَرَ بَدَنَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He anointed his body with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sahiyr","text_ar":"صَهِير"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuhaArap","text_ar":"صُهَارَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saharahu","text_ar":"صَهَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He brought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drew, it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e. a thing, O)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilayohi","text_ar":"اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AShrhu","text_ar":"اصهرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","K","TA","O","AZ"]},{"entry_id":"n25070","headword_ar":"صَهْرٌ","root":"Shr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Roasted, broiled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fried;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$owiY~N","text_ar":"مَشْوِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hot;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAr~N","text_ar":"حَارٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Kr, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n25071","headword_ar":"صِهْرٌ","root":"Shr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Relationship; nearness with respect to kindred;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraAbapN","text_ar":"قَرَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, K:) and ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affinity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sacred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inviolable, tie"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huromap","text_ar":"حُرْمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of relationship consisting in being a father"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brother"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other kinsman of a man's wife:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuhuwrapN","text_ar":"صُهُورَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sacred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inviolable, tie"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huromap","text_ar":"حُرْمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of relationship by marriage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) Fr makes the former word of the fem. gender. (Sgh, TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A relation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kinsman,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kinswoman, of a"},{"kind":"text","text":"man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wife:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kh, S, A, Msb:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a"},{"kind":"text","text":"woman's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"husband:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"father"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brother"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other kinsman of a"},{"kind":"text","text":"woman's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"husband;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hamo'N","text_ar":"حَمْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamN","text_ar":"حَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hmw","text_ar":"حمو"},{"kind":"text","text":")]: (Kh, As, ISk, Msb:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"father"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brother"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other kinsman of a"},{"kind":"text","text":"man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wife:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kh, As, ISk, S, Msb, K:) so accord. to some of the Arabs: (Kh, As, S, Msb:) or none says otherwise, accord. to As, and IAar says the like: (Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any relation of a"},{"kind":"text","text":"man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wife"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a"},{"kind":"text","text":"woman's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"husband whom it is unlawful to marry; as the father,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brother,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"son,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1738},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"paternal uncle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"maternal uncle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":"man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relation by marriage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kinsman of a"},{"kind":"text","text":"man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relation by marriage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man who has married among a people:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Mgh:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"husband of a"},{"kind":"text","text":"man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"daughter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"husband of a"},{"kind":"text","text":"man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sister:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K:) Fr says that, in the Kur xxv. 56, it signifies,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a relation whom it is lawful to marry; as the daughter of a paternal uncle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a maternal uncle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasab","text_ar":"نَسَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the same, a relation whom it is unlawful to marry: Zj, that the former signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a relation whom it is unlawful to marry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter, such as is not a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sihor","text_ar":"صِهْر"},{"kind":"text","text":", of those mentioned in the Kur [iv. 27], from the words “ your mothers are forbidden unto you ” to the words “ and your combining [as your wives] two sisters: ” I'Ab explains"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nsb","text_ar":"نسب"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Shr","text_ar":"صهر"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the former passage of the Kur differently from Fr [altogether], and differently in part from Zj; saying that the former applies to the seven relations first mentioned in iv. 27 in the Kur, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Shr","text_ar":"صهر"},{"kind":"text","text":"to the remaining six there mentioned and that mentioned in the next preceding verse; [so that it includes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":"man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foster-mother, who has suckled him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fostersister, who has been suckled with him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wife's mother;"},{"kind":"text","text":"his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"step-daughter under his guardianship, born of his wife unto whom he has gone in;"},{"kind":"text","text":"his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"son's wife;"},{"kind":"text","text":"his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wife's sister combined with that wife;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"father's wife;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and this, says Az, is correct: (Mgh:) in the Kur xxv. 56, it means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw SihorK","text_ar":"ذُو صِهْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", whether male or female: (Jel:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*awaAtu","text_ar":"ذَوَاتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SihorK","text_ar":"صِهْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Bd:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSohaArN","text_ar":"اَصْهَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K, &c.) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuhoraA='u","text_ar":"صُهْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) which latter is extr. (TA.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SihorapN","text_ar":"صِهْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a female, pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiharaAtN","text_ar":"ضِهَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is app. postclassical.] ―         -b3-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A grave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sepulchre:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, K:) for they used to bury their daughters alive, and say, “ We have married them to the grave: ” then, in the time of El-Islám, this expression was used, and it was said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niEoma AlS~ihoru Alqaboru","text_ar":"نِعْمَ الصِّهْرُ القَبْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An excel-lent son-in-law is the grave"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or it means, correctly, that which supplies the place of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Shr","text_ar":"صهر"},{"kind":"text","text":". (ISd.)"}],"source_refs":["A","K","Mgh","Kh","S","Msb","As","ISk","Az","Lth","IAar","Jel","Bd","ISd"]}]}}